    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Focusing on fiscal discipline by reducing the national debt is arguably the more fundamentally responsible choice for long-term national health. Excessive debt burdens future generations with interest payments that crowd out necessary public investment. While social safety nets are important, an unsustainable debt load can lead to inflation or economic instability that undermines the effectiveness of those very programs. Therefore, tackling the debt first secures the economic platform upon which all social spending must eventually rest.",
      "source": "target",
